title: Televerket (Sweden) - Wikipedia
snippet: Televerket was a Swedish State authority acting as a state-owned corporation (public enterprise), responsible for telecommunications in Sweden from 1853 until 1993. Originally it was named Kongl. Elektriska Telegraf-Werket (literally: Royal Electric Telegraph Agency), which was founded in 1853.

title: Televerket – ett monopols uppgång och fall
snippet: Efter 110 år gick det inte längre att försvara Televerkets monopol. Synen på statens roll hade förändrats och 1993 blev året då telemarknaden öppnades för konkurrens. – Liberalismen hade segrat, säger professor Pontus Braunerhjelm.

title: February 20 in Swedish History - Nordstjernan
snippet: The Swedish end was Kongl. Telegrafverket (founded in 1853 as Konglige Elektriska Telegraf-Werket - literally: Royal Electric Telegraph Agency), later changed to Kungl. Telegrafverket in 1903. The Kungliga (Royal) was dropped in 1946 and the name was further modernized to Televerket in 1953.
